    {
      "text": "Blood during autopsy is preserved in?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "NaF"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "NaCl"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Formalin"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Rectified spirit"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 0,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct Option: A) NaF</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Explanation:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>For toxic analysis, like in alcohol abuse, the ideal <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d3a8a234c61692777196ab718189bf\">preservative</span> for blood is sodium fluoride.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Various methods of preserving viscera:</strong></p>\n\n<ol>\n\t<li>Saturated salt solution</li>\n\t<li>Formalin fixation</li>\n\t<li>Freezing</li>\n\t<li>Alcohol preservation</li>\n\t<li>Formaldehyde solution</li>\n\t<li>Formalin-alcohol solution</li>\n\t<li>Frozen section</li>\n\t<li>Liquid nitrogen</li>\n</ol>\n\n<p><strong>Specimens for Analysis</strong></p>\n\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse\">\n\t<tbody>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Specimen</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Importance</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Blood</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Primary specimen; collect from femoral, iliac, or axillary veins to avoid contamination.</p>\n\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Preservative: </strong>Lithium <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"050e27829716927771885eddb2620c\">heparin</span> or EDTA tube, Sodium fluoride/oxalate <strong>(Option A)</strong>, if alcohol is suspected</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Urine</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Useful for detecting parent compounds and metabolites of poisons.</p>\n\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Preservative: </strong>No preservative, sodium <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"7cdfdfcdc616927772026ac0b8d995\">fluoride</span> is added, if alcohol is</p>\n\n\t\t\t<p>Suspected</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Gastric Contents</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Helps identify ingested poisons and their concentrations through <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"58a09a3d07169277720271320338d4\">vomitus</span> and stomach contents analysis.</p>\n\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Preservative:</strong> Saturated <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"77e95b17ce1692777198780a5d0843\">salt solution</span> if there is no chance of acid poison.<strong>(Option B)</strong></p>\n\n\t\t\t<p>Rectified spirit if poisoned by acid <strong>(Option C)</strong></p>\n\n\t\t\t<p>.</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Liver</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Analyzes <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"5b1a045f5f169277719210c0ac7a1e\">metabolism</span> and concentration of drugs; critical when blood/urine concentrations are low. Bile can detect specific substances like <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"c6cef1cc8616927771849eace61464\">chlorpromazine</span> and morphine.</p>\n\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Preservative:</strong> Saturated <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"77e95b17ce1692777198780a5d0843\">salt solution</span> if there is no chance of acid poison.</p>\n\n\t\t\t<p>Rectified spirit if poisoned by acid.</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Hair and Nails</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Detects <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"6e8ada09fa1692777189bfbace851a\">heavy metal</span> poisoning; metals accumulate in keratin. Neutron <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"ba6b77f29316927771807350f86ce2\">activation</span> analysis identifies specific metals and exposure patterns.</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Scene Residues</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Provides clues about the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b437be3f051692777196d06a1fa93d\">poison</span> through materials found at the scene, such as tablets or empty containers.</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p><strong>Formalin (Option C)</strong> is commonly used for general tissue preservation and <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"71fd4297541692777202797b7596b9\">fixation</span> in <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"116f86834a1692777181a914379270\">anatomical</span> pathology, but it is not specifically preferred for <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"c951767a31169277720004b3ec0817\">toxicology</span> autopsy. It may affect the results of toxicological analyses.</p>",
