    {
      "text": "During a police investigation, some bones are uncovered from the crime scene. Which of the following tests would aid in differentiating between human and canine bones, during the forensic analysis?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Precipitin test"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Acid-phosphatase"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "LDH"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Teichmann test"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 0,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct Option: A) <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"cb77ee11c516927771962af3aaab51\">Precipitin</span> test</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Explanation:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>The test which can give the species <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"55a682d72e16927771865bb4855ba3\">differentiation</span> is the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"cb77ee11c516927771962af3aaab51\">precipitin</span> test.</li>\n\t<li>Precipitin tests can be done by extracting <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"e356ac3111169277719836c6de5972\">species-specific</span> protein from bone into a solution and testing it against specific antisera of humans.</li>\n\t<li>The techniques such as <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"0284ae84d21692777187eb03c87a57\">electrophoresis</span> or <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b0bdc3a1d416927771884d50c944ec\">gel</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"9c760dcb641692777186f4cda5dc95\">diffusion</span> can now identify human tissue.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Confirmatory Tests for Blood Stains in <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d505e5aff31692777203af0565576c\">Forensic</span> Medicine</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Confirmatory tests are critical for identifying blood presence and origin in <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d505e5aff31692777203af0565576c\">forensic</span> investigations.</li>\n\t<li>Methods include chemical, immunological, and mass <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"0e09c228b616927771980cf8a254f0\">spectrometry</span> techniques for reliable results.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Chemical Confirmatory Tests</strong></p>\n\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse\">\n\t<tbody>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Test</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Description</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Takayama Test</strong></p>\n\n\t\t\t<div style=\"text-align:center\">\n\t\t\t<figure class=\"caption_element\" style=\"display:inline-block\"><img alt=\"\" data-author=\"Vanessa Stewart, Paul Deacon, Nathalie Zahra, Mari Uchimoto, Kevin Farrugia\" data-hash=\"\" data-license=\"CC BY NC ND 4.0\" data-source=\"https://rke.abertay.ac.uk/ws/portalfiles/portal/15029667/Farrugia_TheEffectOfMarkEnhancementTechniquesOnThePresumptiveAndConfirmatoryTests_Author_2018.pdf\" data-tags=\"\" height=\"248\" src=\"https://image.prepladder.com/content/gFNaRXm1UZ663vMeJmm21747374880.png\" width=\"500\" />\n\t\t\t<figcaption>{{caption_text}}</figcaption>\n\t\t\t</figure>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Detects <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"ad2073fe6716927771885f3c1ec652\">hemoglobin</span> by forming red, feathery crystals of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"dcccae21671692777196dc33208a39\">pyridine</span> ferroprotoporphyrin.</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Teichmann Test </strong><strong>(Option D ruled out)</strong></p>\n\n\t\t\t<div style=\"text-align:center\">\n\t\t\t<figure class=\"caption_element\" style=\"display:inline-block\"><img alt=\"\" data-author=\"NA\" data-hash=\"\" data-license=\"NA\" data-source=\"https://elearning.raghunathpurcollege.ac.in/files/CE08FC0816227718690.pdf\" data-tags=\"\" height=\"373\" src=\"https://image.prepladder.com/content/7p99mXgegSEqyLmvsuGz1747374893.png\" width=\"500\" />\n\t\t\t<figcaption>{{caption_text}}</figcaption>\n\t\t\t</figure>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Converts <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"ad2073fe6716927771885f3c1ec652\">hemoglobin</span> to hemin, creating brownish-yellow <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"0115afa2131692777197b45ae0d136\">rhomboid</span> crystals, confirming blood presence.</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p><strong>Immunological Tests</strong></p>\n\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse\">\n\t<tbody>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Test</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Description</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Precipitin Test </strong><strong>(Option A)</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Identifies species origin through antibody-antigen reactions, using antisera specific to human blood.</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>HemaTrace Test </strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Uses <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b2b82438d6169277719287eb450079\">monoclonal</span> antibodies to detect human hemoglobin, showing a visible pink band for confirmation.</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p><strong>Mass <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"0e09c228b616927771980cf8a254f0\">Spectrometry</span> Techniques</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li><strong>Thread Spray Mass Spectrometry</strong>: Analyzes <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"60d609888b169277720258496ef45a\">whole blood</span> directly on textiles, differentiating species based on <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"a99114a6c216927771916f45ffc66c\">lipid</span> composition and <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"ad2073fe6716927771885f3c1ec652\">hemoglobin</span> chains. It offers high sensitivity and specificity.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Acid-phosphatase (Option B)</strong> This test can be used to detect seminal fluid.</p>\n\n<p><strong>LDH (Option C)</strong> cannot be used for species differentiation.</p>",
